Eunice Oghinan-Dawodo is a fashion designer, pattern-maker, and author. She has authored several books on garment pattern making and sewing, as well as created numerous garment macros. She has also created a Nigerian sizing standard in the early 2000s, which is already in use for garment production within the country, and is a graduate of History in the University of Benin.Oghinan also owns Ginani Fashion Academy, Ginani eSchool, and eStore. In 2015, she won an award for Best Pattern Making Fashion Academy at the 4th Fashion and Life International Conference and Achievement Awards in Lagos, Nigeria. Oghinan is a member of the Fashion Designers Association of Nigeria.


